snippet.textDisplay:
Just the album cover alone is incredibly evocative and poetic. Never before have I seen an image that perfectly encapsulates the meaning and raw power of a song, but a hand reaching out of lava? Of all the fiery comparisons people have used to describe heartache, nothing is more inevitable, inescapable, or as destructive as the image of someone who is being run down by a seep of magma.
Everything about this song is golden- the beat, the album cover, the vocals, and those absolutely ENCHANTING harmonics! I’m so happy that Joji is overcoming the man who had to quit the Filthy Frank show.
snippet.textOriginal:
Just the album cover alone is incredibly evocative and poetic.  Never before have I seen an image that perfectly encapsulates the meaning and raw power of a song, but a hand reaching out of lava?  Of all the fiery comparisons people have used to describe heartache, nothing is more inevitable, inescapable, or as destructive as the image of someone who is being run down by a seep of magma. 
Everything about this song is golden- the beat, the album cover, the vocals, and those absolutely ENCHANTING harmonics!  I’m so happy that Joji is overcoming the man who had to quit the Filthy Frank show.
